message: Club hopping Ruby Skye, Temple, Bubble Lounge, Starlight Room, and 5A5 Steaklounge.
Check out House of Air at Crissy Field (trampolines) - fun with kids.

I went to the Japanese tea garden in Golden Gate Park this weekend. Admission was a bit pricey, but it's very pleasant, and the tea is good (and not that expensive, when you ignore that you already paid to get in). Doubt I'll be back, but it's a fun thing to do once. http://www.japaneseteagardensf.com/index.php
I don't even drink tea but I friggin' *loved* the tea garden when I visited last summer. Beautiful landscaping :)
There is a nice one down in Saratoga too, Hakone Gardens
There's a TWIT Photo walk happening on the 26th at 2pm - http://www.mostlyphotoadventures.com/
